      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Could it be less potent than expected?** Yes:\n  - The **amide** and **pyridine N** increase polarity and may lower membrane partitioning into the channel vestibule (a factor for apparent hERG potency in cells).\n  - If the molecule\u2019s preferred 3D conformation keeps the **cation too solvated** or misaligned relative to the aromatic bulk, affinity could drop.\n- **Do any features strongly argue \u201cnon-blocker\u201d?** Not really. There is no clear anti-hERG motif like permanent zwitterionic character, multiple strong HBD/HBA patterns causing very low permeability, or lack of aromatic bulk. The dominant pattern remains \u201ccation + hydrophobes\u201d.",
